The paper proposes a deep learning model for predicting long-term and blurry relapses using claims-only databases. This involves handling complex and irregular patterns of health events, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of claims-only databases also suggests a focus on database systems (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL) for extracting relevant information. Finally, the application of the model to medical data suggests a focus on clinical informatics (cs.CE).
